\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1 3/4 pounds {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cherry/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cherry}} or {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/tomato/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 grape tomatoes}}, rinsed and dried\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 teaspoons hot sauce\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 to 3 tablespoons freshly squeezed {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/lemon/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 lemon juice}}, to taste\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 teaspoon kosher salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}6 ounces tomato vodka, recipe follows\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Remove the stems from the tomatoes. Put the tomatoes, hot sauce, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/worcestershire-sauce/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Worcestershire sauce}}, lemon juice, and salt into a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/blender/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 blender}}, cover and blend on high speed for 1 1/2 minutes.\
Fill an ice {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cube/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cube}} tray with about 2 cups of the juice and freeze overnight. Pour the remaining juice into a lidded container and reserve, on the counter, overnight.\
Just before serving, put 3 frozen cubes into each of 4 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/collins/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Collins}} glasses and add 1 1/2 ounces of vodka to each glass. Stir the reserved juice, pour 4 ounces into each glass and serve immediately.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Tomato {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/vodka/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Vodka}}:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1 pound ripe tomatoes\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 (750 ml) bottle 80 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/proof/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 proof}} vodka\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural
\cf0 Cut each of the tomatoes into 8 pieces and put them into a large glass jar. Add the vodka, stir to combine, and cover. Put in a cool, dark place for at least 5 days and up to 7 days, stirring every day. After 7 days, strain through a fine mesh {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/strainer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 strainer}} and discard the solids.\
To store, pour the tomato vodka back into its original bottle, and keep in a cool, dark place.\
Yield: 1 (750 ml) bottle\
